an older brother, too.

10:26.059 --> 10:28.561
You know, I'm using that movie
to find him a girlfriend
so he won't beat me up.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.063
Would he actually
fall for that?

10:30.130 --> 10:31.198
Dude, come on!

10:31.264 --> 10:33.066
Let's go make me
this girl already.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.768
Every week,
he surprises us.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.336
Whoo!
Year of awesome!

10:45.312 --> 10:46.980
ADULT ADAM:
My mom was so psyched
to be spending

10:47.047 --> 10:48.381
the first night
of college with Erica,

10:48.448 --> 10:49.783
she literally couldn't sleep.

10:49.850 --> 10:51.852
Okay, stop.
What are you doing?

10:51.919 --> 10:54.021
Assembling your
safety credenza.

10:54.087 --> 10:57.324
First aid, fire ladder,
canned foods, powdered milk,

10:57.390 --> 10:59.659
and a handheld siren
to alert rescuers

10:59.727 --> 11:00.861
when you're
caught in rubble.

11:00.928 --> 11:02.595
It's really loud.
Want to hear?

11:02.662 --> 11:04.765
I am in college.
I don't need any credenzas.

11:04.832 --> 11:06.666
Now go to bed
before someone finds out

11:06.734 --> 11:08.235
that you're still here.

11:08.301 --> 11:09.236
Evening, Erica.

11:09.302 --> 11:10.570
I wanted to inform
you and Erica

11:10.637 --> 11:11.939
of tonight's freshman mixer

11:12.005 --> 11:13.774
that the school has
mandated me to throw.

11:13.841 --> 11:15.442
"Jamaican' Me Crazy" party?

11:15.508 --> 11:17.711
Ya, mon!

11:17.778 --> 11:18.946
This doesn't come
naturally to me.

11:19.012 --> 11:20.447
Can this be over, now?

11:20.513 --> 11:22.082
As long as you're there.
The kids you meet tonight

11:22.149 --> 11:24.017
might end up being
your friends for life.

11:24.084 --> 11:26.686
Of course, my college friends
are now doctors and lawyers

11:26.754 --> 11:28.121
while I pursue
a foolish dream

11:28.188 --> 11:29.823
of making art
from everyday garbage.

11:29.890 --> 11:31.491
Like Nick
from Family Ties?

11:31.558 --> 11:32.726
It was my idea first.

11:32.793 --> 11:33.961
Anyway, uh,
thanks for the invite,

11:34.027 --> 11:35.863
but I have company
in here already.

11:35.929 --> 11:38.331
As in
romantic company?

11:38.398 --> 11:39.632
Why do you care?

11:39.699 --> 11:41.234
I just don't know what
I'm gonna tell your mother!

11:41.301 --> 11:43.403
She got to you, didn't she?
You've been compromised.

11:44.437 --> 11:46.539
Srini betrayed me!
Open that door.

11:46.606 --> 11:49.843
No way! No one can ever know
about this shameful night.

11:49.910 --> 11:51.211
(ALARM RINGS)

11:51.278 --> 11:52.813
Is that a fire alarm?
I hear a fire alarm.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.647
Mom, relax.
This is college.

11:54.714 --> 11:56.616
Kids pull alarms
every two seconds.

11:56.683 --> 11:58.251
No, you're right.
You're right.

11:58.318 --> 12:00.487
I'll just hang here
and keep a low profile...

12:00.553 --> 12:02.022
And I smell smoke!

12:02.089 --> 12:03.423
Move!
(HANDHELD SIREN BLARES)

12:03.490 --> 12:06.493
Follow the sound of
my hand siren to safety.

12:06.559 --> 12:08.628
Oh, dear. Oh, my.

12:08.695 --> 12:10.964
ADULT ADAM: Mom was right.
Hot plates and dumb
college students do not mix.

12:11.031 --> 12:13.066
Please refer to the pamphlet
on fire evacuation

12:13.133 --> 12:14.667
I provided earlier...

12:14.734 --> 12:16.436
Or just run for your lives!

12:18.638 --> 12:22.209
Make a hole, people!
Make a hole! Make a hole!

12:22.275 --> 12:25.779
Erica Dorothy Goldberg,
you come find your mama!

12:26.579 --> 12:28.415
College is fun.

12:28.481 --> 12:30.217
ADULT ADAM:
While my sister's freshman
year went up in flames,

12:30.283 --> 12:33.120
I had to bring Barry's cool
new girlfriend to life,

12:33.186 --> 12:35.188
or at least make it
seem like that.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.323
Show time.

12:36.389 --> 12:37.457
Let's get weird.

12:37.524 --> 12:40.260
What are my responsibilities
here, again?

12:40.327 --> 12:41.561
I needed bras,

12:41.628 --> 12:42.796
and you're the only guy
I knew who could get them.

12:42.863 --> 12:44.531
Time to hack
into NASA.

12:44.597 --> 12:47.000
ADULT ADAM:
And hack in to NASA we did.

12:47.067 --> 12:49.336
All we needed was my
trusty modem, a little luck,

12:49.402 --> 12:51.471
and my girlfriend
on the other end

12:51.538 --> 12:54.107
pretending to be the most
powerful space agency
in the world.

12:54.174 --> 12:56.109
It's working.
We're making a lady.

12:56.176 --> 12:59.012
ADULT ADAM:
With Barry on board, it was
time for the next phase,

12:59.079 --> 13:00.881
figure out his taste.

13:00.948 --> 13:02.215
ADAM: As you can see,
NASA needs to know

13:02.282 --> 13:04.384
exactly what your
dream-girl looks like.

13:04.451 --> 13:06.353
Again, this is just
between me, you,

13:06.419 --> 13:08.555
the American space program,
and no one else.

13:08.621 --> 13:10.790
That makes me feel safer
about opening up to you.

13:10.858 --> 13:12.225
Sure.
Tell NASA she has to have

13:12.292 --> 13:14.494
Heather Locklear's eyes,
Julia Roberts' smile,

13:14.561 --> 13:17.097
Delta Burke's top stuff,
Bo Derek's hair,

13:17.164 --> 13:18.298
but most important,

13:18.365 --> 13:20.300
Chuck Norris'
sense of justice.

13:20.367 --> 13:22.369
Oy vey.
Time to make that button

13:22.435 --> 13:26.173
and make that closet explode
with lightning and hot ladies.

13:26.239 --> 13:29.209
ADULT ADAM: But, naturally,
Barry's dream woman
didn't exist,

13:29.276 --> 13:30.777
so I had to get
him back on track.

13:30.844 --> 13:32.612
Odd.
It's not working.

13:32.679 --> 13:34.714
What the hell, man?
You promised me a lady.

13:34.781 --> 13:37.417
I already spent a fortune
on candles and erotic oils!

13:37.484 --> 13:39.519
I think the computer
just needs more data,

13:39.586 --> 13:41.821
for example, grounded,
realistic qualities

13:41.889 --> 13:44.691
you could find in women
you'd see in everyday life
or at our school.

13:44.757 --> 13:46.126
Give me that typer!

13:46.193 --> 13:48.161
I'll punch in all the lady
data it can handle.

13:50.030 --> 13:51.731
This list is ridiculous.

13:51.798 --> 13:54.801
How am I supposed
to find a girl who likes
"sensual karate"

13:54.868 --> 13:56.569
and "can kick
a 50-yard field goal"?

13:56.636 --> 13:58.838
Good news is he's looking
for a very specific
kind of gal.

13:58.906 --> 14:01.875
"Ability to communicate
with dolphins
and a savage tan"?

14:01.942 --> 14:03.643
Adam, this list is insane.

14:03.710 --> 14:06.013
Look, this began
with me worrying about
my physical safety,

14:06.079 --> 14:07.915
but now I think Barry
really needs this.

14:07.981 --> 14:09.983
Okay, sure.
I'll try to find someone

14:10.050 --> 14:13.053
with "Morgan Fairchild's
side-butt."

14:13.120 --> 14:14.487
I don't even know
what that is.

14:14.554 --> 14:15.688
I believe in you.

14:15.755 --> 14:17.424
ADULT ADAM: While I put
my faith in Jackie,

14:17.490 --> 14:20.060
my sister was losing faith
that my mom would ever leave.

14:20.127 --> 14:23.563
So, I guess it doesn't matter
if I go on record

14:23.630 --> 14:24.631
and say, "I'm sorry."

14:24.697 --> 14:26.066
No.

14:26.133 --> 14:28.801
I allotted you a very fair
three hours to say goodbye.

14:28.868 --> 14:31.171
Instead, I'm forever known
as the girl who had her mommy

14:31.238 --> 14:33.540
sleep in her dorm
on the first night of school.

14:33.606 --> 14:35.142
Honey, this is college.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.743
There's no judgment here.

14:36.809 --> 14:40.747
(LAUGHS) You let your mom
sleep over on the first night?

14:40.813 --> 14:43.550
Oh, that is very memorable.
(CHUCKLES)

14:43.616 --> 14:44.918
In a negative way.

14:44.985 --> 14:46.186
(LAUGHTER)

14:46.253 --> 14:48.521
That's it.
You are leaving right now,

14:48.588 --> 14:49.923
and never coming back.

14:49.990 --> 14:51.491
The sun's up,
so there are no excuses.

14:51.558 --> 14:53.193
I might have out-stayed
my welcome,

14:53.260 --> 14:56.129
but that's because saying
goodbye is so hard.

14:56.196 --> 14:58.932
No! I'm supposed to be
making life-long friends,

14:58.999 --> 15:00.533
and you took it
away from me

15:00.600 --> 15:02.669
because you refuse
to say goodbye.

15:02.735 --> 15:04.671
Fine.
I'll go.

15:04.737 --> 15:07.107
Right after brunch,
and then we'll spend a few
hours at the Smithsonian,

15:07.174 --> 15:09.943
and then to top it all off,
you have to give Mama
all the kisses.

15:10.010 --> 15:11.878
You can forget about
getting all the kisses.

15:11.945 --> 15:13.313
Not even butterfly?
No!

15:13.380 --> 15:15.915
Surely, Eskimo kisses
are still on the table.

15:15.983 --> 15:17.484
You will never
again experience

15:17.550 --> 15:19.752
the warm nose-love
of our chilly, Native friends.

15:19.819 --> 15:24.057
That is literally
the worst thing a daughter

15:24.124 --> 15:25.892
has ever said to a mother.

15:25.959 --> 15:27.594
(GROANS)

15:27.660 --> 15:29.862
ADULT ADAM:
As Erica swore off
coming home forever,

15:29.929 --> 15:32.065
I swore Jackie and I
had found the perfect girl
for Barry's senior year.

15:32.132 --> 15:35.068
Barry, great news!
I have a girl for you.

15:35.135 --> 15:37.004
Yes!
I knew science was real.

15:37.070 --> 15:39.139
I don't think
that was up for debate.

15:39.206 --> 15:40.907
I meant Jackie
found someone.

15:40.974 --> 15:43.076
You gave her
my lady recipe?

15:43.143 --> 15:44.511
That was for
NASA's eyes only!

15:44.577 --> 15:46.379
I know.
But she found someone

15:46.446 --> 15:48.148
who's got everything
you asked for. Right?

15:48.215 --> 15:50.017
Um, I didn't hit
everything on your list,

15:50.083 --> 15:53.520
but at the top,
you asked for a girl,
and I got that part.

15:53.586 --> 15:55.455
That's not nothing,
mister.

15:55.522 --> 15:56.756
I got goosebumps.

15:56.823 --> 15:58.992
Let's stop talking and bring
out our mystery girl.

15:59.059 --> 16:00.860
Hey! (GIGGLES)

16:00.927 --> 16:03.030
Carla?
Are you insane?

16:03.096 --> 16:04.998
She's a loose cannon,
and not the good kind

16:05.065 --> 16:06.233
like a vigilante cop

16:06.299 --> 16:07.867
who endlessly frustrates
his commissioner.

16:07.934 --> 16:10.503
It's true. The court-appointed
psychiatrist gave up on me.

16:10.570 --> 16:12.205
I didn't even know
you liked me.

16:12.272 --> 16:14.607
I don't. But he dated Lainey,
and she's my rival,

16:14.674 --> 16:16.276
so I'm taking what's hers.

16:16.343 --> 16:18.111
Give me her address so I can
send her photos of us in love.

16:18.178 --> 16:21.314
No. I don't want
this aggressive loony toon
as my special lady.

16:21.381 --> 16:23.450
Well, that's all we got.
Thanks, Adam.

16:23.516 --> 16:25.685
You've officially made
a mockery of our plan

16:25.752 --> 16:27.787
to have a computer
print out a girl for me.

16:27.854 --> 16:29.822
Oh, my God, dude!

16:29.889 --> 16:31.691
Weird Science isn't real!

16:31.758 --> 16:34.361
There will never be
a year of awesome

16:34.427 --> 16:36.363
or girls fighting over you
in a Thunderdome,

16:36.429 --> 16:38.898
and you're not gonna
live with Kathy Ireland!

16:38.965 --> 16:41.101
All you are is Barry!

16:41.801 --> 16:43.336
Believe me. I know.

16:43.403 --> 16:45.004
And I know that movie's
just a movie.

16:45.072 --> 16:46.439
Then why did you...

16:46.506 --> 16:48.208
I just wanted to believe
things would be okay.

16:48.275 --> 16:50.143
That... That...

16:50.210 --> 16:52.279
Lainey wasn't a fluke.

16:52.345 --> 16:53.746
That someone would actually
love me again.

16:54.947 --> 16:56.216
Barry...
No.

16:57.584 --> 16:59.219
You're right.

16:59.286 --> 17:01.054
Looks like I'm back
to being me.

17:06.626 --> 17:08.795
ADULT ADAM: Thanks to me,
Barry had hit rock bottom,

17:08.861 --> 17:11.131
so it was time for me
to get him back on top.

17:11.198 --> 17:12.532
What's this?

17:12.599 --> 17:14.000
I've revised your daily
ass-kicking schedule

17:14.067 --> 17:15.202
for your year of awesome.

17:15.268 --> 17:16.736
Go away.
I don't need your pity.

17:16.803 --> 17:19.072
Before you reject my offer,
I think you'll agree

17:19.139 --> 17:21.208
that I've really jazzed up
your options.

17:21.274 --> 17:23.376
No.
Yes.

17:23.443 --> 17:26.579
You get to pants me in public,
and not just anywhere,

17:26.646 --> 17:29.916
at the first pep rally
of the year.

17:29.982 --> 17:32.018
In front of
the entire school?

17:32.085 --> 17:34.587
That'd be the Holy Grail of
younger-brother humiliation.

17:34.654 --> 17:36.756
Indeed. And I'm offering
it to you wearing this.

17:38.591 --> 17:40.360
Sweat pants?

17:40.427 --> 17:42.729
That's a loose garment
ideal for pantsing.

17:42.795 --> 17:43.830
But it gets better.

17:43.896 --> 17:45.098
ADULT ADAM: It really did.

17:45.165 --> 17:46.666
I then presented Barry
with the ultimate

17:46.733 --> 17:49.102
little-brother sacrifice,
my drawstring.

17:49.169 --> 17:50.803
The uncinched sweats
will be loose

17:50.870 --> 17:52.939
beyond your wildest dreams.

17:53.005 --> 17:54.374
Have you gone mad?

17:54.441 --> 17:56.008
To get you back to your
rightful place on top,

17:56.075 --> 17:57.277
I would rip the drawstring

17:57.344 --> 17:59.546
from every loose-fitting
pant I own.

17:59.612 --> 18:02.815
Wow, you really
are a good brother.

18:02.882 --> 18:04.284
But

18:04.351 --> 18:05.985
none of this changes the fact
that Lainey's gone

18:06.052 --> 18:07.520
and I'll never find
anyone like her.

18:07.587 --> 18:09.589
Listen, Weird Science
might not be real,

18:09.656 --> 18:11.858
but you'll find
your dream girl.

18:11.924 --> 18:13.059
I know it in my heart.

18:13.126 --> 18:14.627
You think?
Of course.

18:14.694 --> 18:17.630
Someone's gonna see
what Lainey saw in you,

18:17.697 --> 18:19.031
what I see in you.

18:19.098 --> 18:20.800
and that's a legend.

18:20.867 --> 18:22.502
Thanks.

18:22.569 --> 18:24.537
I don't know whether
to give you a hug
or a butt hat.

18:24.604 --> 18:26.539
Both sound
very uncomfortable.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.276
Let's start with this.

18:29.342 --> 18:30.943
ADULT ADAM: With that,
I helped Barry realize

18:31.010 --> 18:33.680
that he could still have
an epic senior year,

18:33.746 --> 18:36.048
even if it wasn't
quite what he imagined.

18:36.115 --> 18:37.217
Morning, or whatever.

18:37.284 --> 18:39.486
Same clothes.
Fun night?

18:39.552 --> 18:41.053
From what I hear,
not as fun as the night

18:41.120 --> 18:42.922
you had with your mommy?

18:42.989 --> 18:45.858
So, want to help me
take down all this crap?

18:45.925 --> 18:49.396
ADULT ADAM:
That day, Erica finally
got her new start

18:49.462 --> 18:51.431
by letting go of the past.

18:51.498 --> 18:54.301
But sometimes
that's not so easy.

18:54.367 --> 18:55.835
That's a cute photo.

18:55.902 --> 18:57.704
ERICA: It was the first day
of kindergarten.

18:57.770 --> 19:02.375
I was so scared, and she
stayed with me the whole day.

19:02.442 --> 19:04.711
That's a good mom.

19:05.678 --> 19:08.448
Damn it,
why do I miss her?

19:08.515 --> 19:10.583
Seriously, something's
wrong with me.

19:10.650 --> 19:14.020
I mean, yeah, your folks
are weird and intrusive,

19:14.086 --> 19:15.855
but they were here.

19:17.190 --> 19:19.792
My parents were
too busy to come.

19:19.859 --> 19:21.228
And that's bad?

19:21.294 --> 19:23.363
I didn't think it was until
I saw your mother cared enough

19:23.430 --> 19:25.665
to bring your home right here.

19:26.799 --> 19:27.734
You're lucky.

19:27.800 --> 19:29.436
ADULT ADAM: And,
thanks to Erica,

19:29.502 --> 19:32.605
Erica realized
how fortunate she really was.

19:32.672 --> 19:35.174
"Bad night vision"?
Really?

19:35.242 --> 19:36.643
That is a real thing.

19:36.709 --> 19:39.011
I hear my dad complaining
about it all the time.

19:39.078 --> 19:40.213
Hey.

19:40.280 --> 19:41.614
(GASPS)
My baby's back!

19:41.681 --> 19:43.483
Mom, I'm just
here to say goodbye.

19:43.550 --> 19:46.018
So, you don't hate me?

19:46.085 --> 19:49.656
Look, I know I've been pushing
you away since we got here.

19:50.890 --> 19:53.260
I guess it's just
easier to do that

19:53.326 --> 19:55.862
than actually accept
that this is it.

19:57.464 --> 19:58.765
So, now what?

19:58.831 --> 20:00.500
ADULT ADAM:
And so, after everything,

20:00.567 --> 20:02.702
my mom got exactly
what she wanted.

20:02.769 --> 20:04.437
The idea that leaving
for college

20:04.504 --> 20:07.240
was just as hard for
my sister as it was for her.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.642
And one last kiss
in your palm

20:09.709 --> 20:13.179
for you to ball up
and stick in your heart.

20:13.246 --> 20:14.714
* Just half a chance

20:14.781 --> 20:17.216
* Make sure that
one night you're here

20:17.284 --> 20:19.085
* But next night, you're not

20:19.151 --> 20:21.788
ADULT ADAM:
As for Barry, well,
he realized his senior year

20:21.854 --> 20:25.124
could be a little easier
if he teamed up with me.

20:25.191 --> 20:27.059
Here you go,
little bro.

20:27.126 --> 20:28.428
* Tenderness

20:28.495 --> 20:30.162
* Tenderness

20:30.229 --> 20:31.898
* Tenderness

20:31.964 --> 20:33.800
It's kind of sweet
how you look after
your little brother.

20:33.866 --> 20:35.768
Yeah?

20:35.835 --> 20:38.738
Um, yeah.

20:38.805 --> 20:40.573
Thanks.

20:40.640 --> 20:42.375
ADULT ADAM: In the end,
you'd be surprised

20:42.442 --> 20:45.111
what a little help
from your loved ones
can do for you.

20:45.177 --> 20:46.779
No matter how far away
you are,

20:46.846 --> 20:49.449
you can always keep
a little piece of home

20:49.516 --> 20:51.418
close to your heart.

20:52.519 --> 20:53.953
* Tenderness

21:06.032 --> 21:08.301
Oh, hey, Jackie.
Are you staying for dinner?

21:08.368 --> 21:10.570
I'm making chicken-fried
chicken Parm.

21:10.637 --> 21:13.072
Thanks, but I should
just get going.

21:13.139 --> 21:14.441
BOTH: Eskimo kiss.

21:14.507 --> 21:15.508
Butterfly kiss.

21:15.575 --> 21:17.377
Cheek kiss.
Cheek kiss.

21:17.444 --> 21:18.878
And one last kiss in your palm

21:18.945 --> 21:21.314
so you can ball it up
and stick it in your heart.

21:22.649 --> 21:25.117
I, uh, taught her
all the kisses.

21:25.184 --> 21:26.719
You don't mind, do you?

21:28.955 --> 21:30.056
Oh.
